{"add":{"doc":{"id":"eb5009a40d543ee1e9f39badc043ad6dbbc35334821cd92ad545fd8215d530d0","url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/40/Wfm_baffin_island.jpg/250px-Wfm_baffin_island.jpg","previous":[],"after":["The relocation has been a source of controversy: on one hand being described as a humanitarian gesture to save the lives of starving native people and enable them to continue a subsistence lifestyle; and on the other hand, said to be a forced migration instigated by the federal government to assert its sovereignty in the Far North, in light of both the Cold War and the disputed territorial claims to the Arctic archipelago. Both sides acknowledge that the relocated Inuit were not given sufficient support during their first years after the move to prevent extreme privation."]}}}